<TITLE> DU to honour Turkish president </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 31 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka University's administration has decided to give an honorary doctorate to the Turkish president Abdullah Gul on Sunday. A special academic council decided to give Gul a Doctor of Laws degree. DU vice chancellor Prof AAMS Arefin Siddique revealed this decision on Sunday. He also said that the university chancellor, and president of Bangladesh, Zillur Rahman will hand over the at Nawab Ali Chowdhury Senate Bhaban on Feb 13. He said that the decision to honour Gul with this degree was taken for his contribution in fields of education, research and politics of Turkey. Abdullah Gul is scheduled to visit Bangladesh on Feb 12 on a state invitation. He served as Turkey's foreign minister, deputy prime minister and prime minister before becoming the president. bd
